            "text": "Legionella pneumophila serotype 1 (BinaxNOW Legionella; Abbot, Lake Bluff, IL, USA), which has almost 100% specificity, was positive. Chest radiography was not clinically significant, but chest computed tomography showed bilateral, patchy, peripheral ground-glass opacity ( Figure 2 ). 500 mg azithromycin and 2 g ceftriaxone were initiated. Although",
